Guide to install eEva's dependencies and running the application
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Required software:
- nodejs
- mongodb
- Webstorm (optional; only for modifying the application; js mainframe is independent)

-------------------------------------------------------------------

1) upgrade nodejs to v8 (latest version has issues)

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install curl
$ curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_8.x | sudo -E bash -
$ sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

-------------------------------------------------------------------

2) install node modules (cd to project root, where public, server, client etc folders are located)

$ npm install .

-------------------------------------------------------------------

3) install bower 

$ sudo -H npm install -g bower

3.1) install bower components (cd to public folder, see doc/eEVA_Parse_InstallationManual.pdf for extra details)

$ bower install

-------------------------------------------------------------------

4) Restore mongo database from a dump by using the following command:

$ mongorestore --drop -d eEvaParse mongodump-2018-09-11_11-04\eEvaParse

Note: the actual database dump folder might be different (see blank-slate version by Emmanuel)

-------------------------------------------------------------------

5) Launch the application (cd to root):

$ ./start.sh

-------------------------------------------------------------------

6) Open Google Chrome and access http://localhost:3013 -- ensure you are connected to the internet for speech recognition and synthesis to work.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
(optional)
*) in webstorms, after following tutorial (see doc/eEVA_Parse_InstallationManual.pdf), add the following (bogus) environment variables:

